    <div class="info-section">
        <h3>About the Community Design Jams</h3>
        <p>After the spring series, each community partner presents a real challenge they need help solving. Participants—students, neighbors, professionals, creatives—form teams and join a two-week design sprint. The process starts asynchronously and culminates in a <strong>live hybrid pitch session</strong> to community stakeholders. Teams must pitch to be eligible for prizes.</p>
        <p>Each Jam is supported by a multidisciplinary Jefferson student <strong>Jam Leader</strong> who guides teams, connects them with community partners and resources, and keeps momentum throughout the sprint.</p>
        <h3 style="margin-top:32px;">Prizes & Opportunities</h3>
        <div class="prizes-grid">
            <div class="prize-item"><strong>Cash Awards</strong>$250–$500 monetary prizes sponsored by event partners</div>
            <div class="prize-item"><strong>Continued Collaboration</strong>Opportunities to keep working with the community partner and Health Design Lab</div>
            <div class="prize-item"><strong>Mentorship</strong>Access to industry and community leaders</div>
            <div class="prize-item"><strong>Recognition</strong>Features in university publications and media channels</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</div>
    <div class="faq-section">
        <div class="expandable-card">
            <div class="expandable-header"><h3>Why This Series Matters</h3><span class="expand-icon">+</span></div>
            <div class="expandable-content">
                <p>This series highlights the <strong>do-ers in Philadelphia</strong>—the organizers, caregivers, and advocates who work tirelessly to promote health in our communities, one person at a time. These conversations do more than inform—they activate.</p>
                <p>Everything learned in the spring directly fuels the JeffSolves 2026 Community Design Jams, where participants come together to brainstorm and build solutions. The stories, challenges, and insights shared during the series become the foundation for the design challenges issued by our community partners.</p>
                <p>By the time Summer 2026 arrives, participants will understand the issues, know the people involved, and be ready to collaborate.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="expandable-card">
            <div class="expandable-header"><h3>This Series is for YOU</h3><span class="expand-icon">+</span></div>
            <div class="expandable-content">
                <p>Anyone who is frustrated with the current state of health and healthcare and is searching for a way to be part of the solution. <strong>Whether you work in healthcare or not, if you believe health is a human right, you belong in this conversation.</strong></p>
                <p>This is a <strong>low-barrier event</strong> designed for anyone who wants to learn. You don't need prior experience in health or healthcare—just curiosity, openness, and a belief that health matters. These gatherings are welcoming spaces to hear stories, ask questions, and connect with people doing the work on the ground.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="expandable-card">
            <div class="expandable-header"><h3>What to Expect</h3><span class="expand-icon">+</span></div>
            <div class="expandable-content">
                <p>Four sessions held in different locations around Philadelphia, each featuring the doers, advocates, and community health champions improving access to care every day. Discussions are followed by a brief facilitated networking opportunity.</p>
                <p style="background:#f9f9f9;padding:20px;border-radius:12px;margin-top:20px;border-left:4px solid #4a90a4;"><strong>Support the Do-ers:</strong> We ask that attendees make a meaningful monetary contribution when registering, although it is not required. A minimum donation of $10 is suggested, and <strong>100% of these funds will be donated directly to the presenting organization.</strong></p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="expandable-card">
            <div class="expandable-header"><h3>Who We Are</h3><span class="expand-icon">+</span></div>
            <div class="expandable-content">
                <p><strong>Health Tech PHL</strong> — Our goal is to facilitate connections between all the players in the Philadelphia region: entrepreneurs, clinicians, technologists, activists, and builders. We're interested in connecting people who recognize healthcare as a key opportunity: how do we make it more efficient, more equitable, and more effective, so that it reflects the aspirations of our country, the best of our communities, and the brilliance of humans.</p>
                <p><strong>Jefferson Health Design Lab</strong> — A hub for human-centered innovation at Jefferson, bringing together students, clinicians, designers, and community partners to create solutions that improve health and healthcare access. This year, we celebrate <strong>10 years of promoting better health through better design.</strong></p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="expandable-card">
            <div class="expandable-header"><h3>Is there a cost to attend?</h3><span class="expand-icon">+</span></div>
            <div class="expandable-content"><p>Free to attend. A suggested $10 contribution supports the presenting community organization—100% donated directly to them.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="expandable-card">
            <div class="expandable-header"><h3>Do I have to attend all four conversations or all four Jams?</h3><span class="expand-icon">+</span></div>
            <div class="expandable-content"><p>No—attend as many as you like. But the more conversations you join, the better prepared you'll be for the summer Design Jams. Each Jam is a standalone event; join one or all of them.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="expandable-card">
            <div class="expandable-header"><h3>Do I need a team to join a Design Jam?</h3><span class="expand-icon">+</span></div>
            <div class="expandable-content"><p>No. You can sign up solo—teams will form at the start of each Jam. Attending the Conversation Series makes team formation easier and more natural!</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="expandable-card">
            <div class="expandable-header"><h3>How much time is involved in a Design Jam?</h3><span class="expand-icon">+</span></div>
            <div class="expandable-content"><p>A flexible few hours per week over two weeks. Work is mostly asynchronous with optional check-ins and a required final pitch. Pitches are hybrid so anyone can participate remotely, but teams must pitch to be eligible for prizes.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="expandable-card">
            <div class="expandable-header"><h3>Do I have to do the Jams if I attend the conversations?</h3><span class="expand-icon">+</span></div>
            <div class="expandable-content"><p>No—but you'll probably want to! Many attendees get inspired by the spring conversations and choose to return for the summer Jams to put their ideas into action.</p></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

